Date: Wed, 9 Nov 1983  19:30 EST
Message-ID: <ECC.11966354942.BABYL@MIT-OZ>
From: Eugene Ciccarelli <ECC%MIT-OZ@MIT-MC.ARPA>
To:   Babyl-Installers@MIT-MC
cc:   BUG-BABYL@MIT-MC
Subject: New Babyl

New Babyl files on OZ, ML, MC, and XX, e.g.:

XX: PS:<EMACS>BABYL.EMACS
XX: PS:<EMACS>BABYLM.EMACS
XX: PS:<INFO>BABYL.INFO

Babyl changes (BABYLM, actually) involve correcting an oversight
on my part:  I only recently became aware that RFC822 requires
more quoting in the personal name field.  For instance, if
periods are in the name, quoting must be used, as in:

    "Eugene C. Ciccarelli" <ECC at MIT-OZ>

or many other variants, including:

    Eugene C\. Ciccarelli <ECC at MIT-OZ>

So, in view of this, when Babyl parses the recipient fields in
outgoing mail, it may add quoting to the personal name field.
In parsing for header reformation, however, it will REMOVE
quoting around the personal name in most cases (it is
conservative).  Thus the first example above would get the
quoting removed, and so Babyl users should not in general notice
the change.  (They will if they have reformation turned off.)

Also:  The Babyl INFO node now has command and option
abstracts for the BBOARD library too, following those for the
BABYL library commands/options.

