    USER-HEADER;210
    References: The message of 9 November 1983 17:24 EST from KMP @ MIT-MC,
		The message of 9 November 1983 22:39 EST from KMP @ MIT-MC
    USER-HEADER:Postal-Address: 545 Technology Square, Cambridge, MA  02139
    TEXT;-1
    Boy does this win.

produces mail like the following...

    Date: 12 November 1983 18:04 EST
    From: Kent M. Pitman <KMP @ MIT-MC>
    To: KMP @ MIT-MC
    Postal-Address: 545 Technology Square, Cambridge, MA  02139
    References: The message of 9 November 1983 17:24 EST from KMP @ MIT-MC,
		The message of 9 November 1983 22:39 EST from KMP @ MIT-MC
    In-Reply-To: Your msg of 12-Nov-83 18:01-EST

    Boy does this win.

Note that the header fields are still reversed. That's a COMSAT bug which
I would still muchly like to see fixed, but it doesn't get confused about
the References information.

The convention for these request files, in case you've forgotten is
    LABEL:<text-to-end-of-line><crlf>
or
    LABEL;<char-count><crlf>
    <possibly-multi-line-text><crlf>

where <char-count> is in octal (or decimal if followed by ".")
and should not count either the crlf after the "LABEL;<char-count>"
or on the last line of the the text (counting that <crlf> will tend to
force a double-<crlf> in the header area, something COMSAT doesn't 
check for as it forms messages, and make the header area end prematurely).

