It really isn't an error -- it is just a spurious message.  That
is of course a bug, but not a UVN bug.  There is some strange
interaction between errsets, throws, and Teco's top-level catch (@<...>)
or something.  Your Babyl file has an option that Babyl doesn't
recognize, though it doesn't really care.  It finds that out with
something like:

      1:< q2uBabyl 1 Option >w

This quietly ignores the UVN error that happens within that
errset.  However, this (the & Reset Babyl Options routine) is
being called during the exit from Edit Babyl Options -- it is an
unwind handler.  Edit Babyl Options is throwing a 0 value to the
top level Babyl command loop, but I think somehow that catch is
getting a non-0 value, the UVN message.  I'm not sure about this
last bit, but I know for sure that both Edit Babyl Options and
its unwind handler & Reset Babyl Options are both exiting, not
aborting part-way through.

Anyway, until this is cleared up, here's what you can do:  First,
you might as well delete GUMBY;BADBAB ECC, since I now know how
to reproduce the error.  And second, whenever you want, do an
Edit Babyl Options and just ignore the message...

