I actually prefer the recommendations of RFC822 for the following reasons:

 * It is extremely important (in regards to Randy Davis's gripe last
   week) that there be a way for a sender of a message to advise
   mail readers of the entire intended return list. This is useful for
   polls ("How many users do X?"), and requests for info. It is simply
   not realistic to expect people to heed a PS that says "reply only to
   me, not the whole list"; experience says such notes are frequently
   ignored.

 * We already have a way to over-ride only the From field: by providing
   an explicit From field. ie, if I write

	From:KMP
	To:BUG-BABYL
	--...

   when in a Babyl on someone else's console, it will come through as

	From: KMP
