Date: 28 Feb 1984  09:28 MST (Tue)
Message-ID: <WANCHO.11995365181.BABYL@SIMTEL20>
From: "Frank J. Wancho" <WANCHO@SIMTEL20>
To:   David Vinayak Wallace <GUMBY@MIT-MC>
Cc:   BUG-BABYL@MIT-MC, WANCHO@SIMTEL20
Subject: how to confuse babyl completely
In-reply-to: Msg of 28 Feb 1984  03:08-MST from David Vinayak Wallace <GUMBY at MIT-MC>

Dave,

The mistake was not using ^X^F in the first place, and then simply ^XB
to select the *Mail* buffer again.  The reason is that you were
already in a recursive edit mode under BABYL.  However, by doing ^XR,
you "recursed" a second time rather than pop a level to continue the
BABYL you already in.  By starting a second-level BABYL, the hooks
left from the first level did not allow you to Continue, since you
were still "sending mail" as far as it was concerned.  By then, you
were already too deep in the nesting to actually try to send.

If you had Quit or ^X'd that second level BABYL, then selected the
*Mail* buffer, you could have picked up where you left off and sent
that message under the first-level BABYL, and all would have been
"right" again.

--Frank

