In-reply-to: Msg of 30 Jul 1984  20:33-EDT from Adam G. Mellis <Mellis>

There are two cases where Babyl won't write back  changes:
First, if you have read in a Babyl file that specifies an Owner
and you aren't it.  Second, if you have read in a mail file, not
a Babyl file.  That is, some file that has a mail-file format,
not Babyl-file format, such as a MAIL.TXT file.  Babyl's
philosophy is that you read in a mail file (the in-box), make
changes, and file them to a Babyl file, not back to the original
mail file.  The solution is to create a Babyl file for that mail
file.  (You can have any number of Babyl files -- each specifies
its own mail file.)

Do either of these cases sound like what you are encountering?

