Your first question says it's asking about "ranges", but then
proceeds to talk about sets (or sequences, if you prefer) of
messages that match some predicate.  Babyl doesn't understand
ranges (by which I mean messages n through m) and probably won't
in the near future.  However, it does have a set capability,
using its labeling mechanism.  (When ZBabyl gets officially
installed this situation will improve.  ZBabyl has a much more
power filtering capability.)

Here's how you could approximate your
example (moving messages from <user> to a file):

First, label all messages containing some string that you think
will best approximate the "from <user>" match, e.g., for messages
from FooBar, attaching some label, e.g., flame:

    M-X Label Messages Containing StringFooBarflame<return>

Then output all messages labeled flame to the file:

    M-X Output Labeled Messages<return>

It will ask for the label, the filename, whether to remove the
label, and whether to mark these messages as deleted.

You might interpose a middle step that surveys the messages
labeled flame, to check that these are the right ones.  If not,
you can trim it further by going into Survey Menu to remove some
of the labels.

