Unfortunately, that will split it at random places, so if you want to
read the split files using mail-reading software (as opposed to just
looking at them in Emacs), you have to adjust them to break on message
boundaries.  This requires some knowledge of the mail format, so let
me know if you need to do this and I'll do it for you.  There really
should be a M-X Split Mail File command in SPLIT...

