Sigh.

No.  "& Append..." is, as its name suggests, a subroutine, and not
intended to be accessible as an extended command.  The appropriate
extended command would be 

			M-X # Babyl ^O

This will take a string argument, in the form

		   M-X # Babyl ^OFOO.BAR

As will just plain ^O.

If you do not give a string-arg, both ^O and the extended command 
default to the string defined in the variable Babyl ^O Filename.  
Absent a definition, it comes up FOO.TXT in Babyl 772.

