It's very complicated to do that for now. There are a lot of efficiency 
issues and a few interface issues to be worked out. It's been discussed and
even thought through fairly carefully but can't easily be done.

Recent changes to ZBabyl make it possible to export and use transparently
as if it were merged with Babyl. If you pick up the following files you
should be able to run it by just setting mail reader library to ZMAIL:

 [XX]PS:<EMACS>TPARSE.EMACS.137
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>TPARSE.^V:EJ.137
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>ZBABYL.LISP.1
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>ZBABYL.EMACS.42
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>ZBABYL.^V:EJ.42
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>ZMENU.EMACS.20
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>ZMENU.^V:EJ.20
 [XX]PS:<INFO>ZBABYL.INFO.4

The root INFO node doesn't point to the ZBabyl documentation. You have to
edit in a ZBabyl node that points to the <INFO> node mentioned here if you
think that's appropriate for your site.

If you have Lisp Machines at your site, you will probably want 
the following additional files which allow you to use the Lisp Machine
mouse with ZBabyl (or vanilla Emacs, for that matter) when netting
into your Tops-20 over Supdup or Telnet.

 [XX]PS:<EMACS>EMOUSE.EMACS.3
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>EMOUSE.^V:EJ.3
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>EMOUSE.LISP.1
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>EMOUSE.SOURCE.18		;Source to the following 5 files
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>EMOUSE.REL4-BIN.4	;Symbolics LM-2 Rel4 binary
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>EMOUSE.REL4-QBIN.4	;Symbolics 3600 Rel4 binary
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>EMOUSE.REL5-BIN.4	;Symbolics 3600 Rel5 binary
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>EMOUSE.REL6-BIN.1	;Symbolics 3600 Rel6 binary
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>EMOUSE.SYS98-QFASL.2	;MIT CADR System 98 binary
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>ZMOUSE.EMACS.2
 [XX]PS:<EMACS>ZMOUSE.^V:EJ.2

If you have another system than the LispM systems I've provided bin files
for, just compile <EMACS>EMOUSE.SOURCE to the appropriate file name (see
<EMACS>EMOUSE.LISP to see what's going on).

Note: The ^V in all of the above names wants to be a real Control-V, of course.

I believe there is a known bug that makes *FILE-FILTER-DAEMONS* not work quite
right on Twenex, but other than that I think everything should mostly work.
Please report any ZBabyl problems to BUG-ZBABYL@MIT-MC so that BUG-BABYL doesn't
get cluttered with irrelevant stuff.

