    screwed something up. -- Steve

The "Owner" field in the Babyl Options section must contain your user
name literally. Babyl compares the user's name against that field and
will not modify the Babyl file or mail file if the name does not match.
Only
	Owner: SJG
will work. Things like 
	Owner: Steven J. Gordon <SJG at OZ>
will not work unless you can figure out how to log in with the user
name "Steven J. Gordon <SJG at OZ>".


