Subject: Overquoting MMAILR-queued messages

Given a From: line of the form:

"Webb Mike"@LLL-MFE

BABYL does not remove the double quotes when building the envelope for
the queue file in a reply.  This causes MMAILR to add additional
backslash quoting which is dutifully stripped at LLL-MFE and results
in an unrecognized address there.

According to Mark:

     MMailr requires that SMTP quotes NOT be in the envelope; it
applies SMTP quoting itself.  If a quote appears in the envelope,
MMailr assumes that the quote is a significant character in the
address and will backslash-quote the quote!

     This is NOT, repeat, NOT an MMailr bug.  This is the way the
queued mail file functionality is designed, and implemented, and used
by MM with quoted addresses.

