    I am having trouble with large files. Buffer exhausted blather. 
    Whats the fix for this? Thanxs

Babyl's address space is non-extensible, so when your Babyl file gets
big, the only thing you can do is delete messages. You can, however,
move them to other files (using the "O" command) before deleting them.
There are commands for moving back and forth between files (eg, see
the "I" command) which involve writing out the whole file you're viewing,
then recycling the space it was using to read in the new file.

You might look into ZBabyl. It takes advantage of some ideas from the
Lisp Machine Zmail program to make some of these things easier. It has
the disadvantage that it takes more space than regular Babyl, and so 
the Babyl files you can fit are even smaller, but its advantage is that 
it makes mail reading more efficient, which may be worth the price.
ZBabyl is just a Babyl extension and uses the same file format as Babyl,
so you can go back and forth between them. ZBabyl is documented in Info
(from Emacs, type c-X I); report problems to Bug-ZBabyl@MC. Good luck.
-kmp


