Subject: Babyl robustness
cc:   Doug@SU-CSLI.ARPA

If you are logged out before writing your Babyl file then you lose all
your recent mail.  This is because your recent mail is in a deleted
file ([BABYL.<username>) and your directory is expunged on logout.
The same thing could happen if you expunged and reset your Babyl fork.

I propose that the [BABYL.<username> file is not deleted until a write
is done (w/ either Q or S commands).  This way no matter what happens,
if you lose your Babyl fork without writing the file, Babyl will
notice that their was a crash and read in the lost messages.


