This fairly long-standing bug in ZBabyl (originally reported by FJW) 
has finally been fixed.

For those interested, the bug was due to the fact that Babyl had a
macro (& Babyl Append) whose name was a proper substring of a ZBabyl 
macro name (& Babyl Append Refs). Because of the way the named-macro
finder works in Teco, doing m(m.m& Babyl Append) was finding the 
wrong macro.

This bug only struck if you appended mail to your babyl file (most of 
us at MIT prepend). That, combined with the fact that if you just read
the code, it looked fine, was what took so long to track it down.

Apologies for the delay in this fix.


