    Can someone tell me what to do in situations like this?  Is there some
    way to answer its prompts so that I can get to my new mail (outside of
    using mm!).

No. There's not much of a good solution once you get to this point other
than extreme actions such as using MM, Zmail, or whatever -- even using
bare Emacs -- to edit your mail file down to something manageable. The
pdp10 address space is only 256K 36-bit words and when it's used up, many
programs can't do better -- Teco/Emacs/Babyl, for example. MM plays special
games that let it handle larger mail files, but eventually you will find
that it loses, too.

Preventative measures work better. That is, don't let your mail pile up.
If you find you're holding onto a lot of back mail, use the O command to
move the mail to move the mail to auxiliary files.

If you really just can't keep up no matter what you try, you should probably
find a Lisp Machine somewhere and start using Zmail on a regular basis.


