Hi.  You and I seem to be the only ones touching Babyl recently.  So
before (or instead of) asking the Bug-Babyl list, let me ask you this.
It seems that the Babyl sources themselves think that the canonical
source location for Babyl is MC.  This no longer works for a whole
bunch of reasons (no such directories, etc).  MX is also a poor
choice.  The BABYL-INSTALLERS list on MC seems to imply that non-XX
people should get notified when a new Babyl is installed there.  On
the other hand, the only version currently on XX is one with "local
changes" by you, hence probably not good for distribution.  You're
also not on *any* of the Babyl-whatever lists (dunno if this is an
oversight or deliberate), so I don't know if whomever makes changes to
Babyl on XX (only you?) announces them.

In view of all this (and because I've been doing a little hacking of
late), I am tempted to make OZ the canonical location for Babyl
sources.  It's time to decide this for real, because the most recent
changes that have been made are on Twenex, not ITS, and they have
started to diverge (you've made local changes to XX, and I do not know
if they can be transported).

Now, no matter which way this goes (wherever the latest sources are
supposed to live), I'd like to bring OZ's and XX's Babyl back into
correspondence.  At this particular instant, by removing your changes
on XX, they would be correspondent---but I'm about to release a
slightly changed version on OZ.  Is it a good idea for me to simply
merge in your XX changes to the version I'll release on OZ?  Will they
work on ITS and hence all the sources everywhere can agree?

Thanx much.

