Subject:  Correct RFC822 syntax not understood by BABYL.
To: BUG-BABYL@MC.LCS.MIT.EDU
Message-ID: <[AI.AI.MIT.EDU].117287.861111.JAR>

In ZBABYL 41 in NEX 355, Emacs 162, Teco 1171, ITS 1587 on MIT-AI:

An address spec with routing information in it, e.g.

    From: Jonathan Rees <@AI:JAR@AI>

causes BABYL to complain about illegal syntax.  I checked RFC822, and to
my surprise I found that in fact this is legal.

I get messages like this moderately often, so this is somewhat annoying.
It's no big deal, but I thought I should report it.

[The details, if you're interested:
     address     =  mailbox                      ; one addressee
                 /  group                        ; named list
     group       =  phrase ":" [#mailbox] ";"
     mailbox     =  addr-spec                    ; simple address
                 /  phrase route-addr            ; name & addr-spec
     route-addr  =  "<" [route] addr-spec ">"
     route       =  1#("@" domain) ":"           ; path-relative
     addr-spec   =  local-part "@" domain        ; global address
]

Jonathan

