messages from a MAIL.TXT file based on the values of the well-known MM
bit flags.  Ie, I got tired of BABYL discarding information about which
messages I had already seen with MM.  MM's "FLAGGED" maps to RemindNow,
UNSEEN, ANSWERED, and DELETED map to the obvious, the rest are user
flags that can't be deciphered without the user's MM.INIT file so I
didn't try.  The code runs slower than I'd wish, but this is only an
issue if you're babylizing a MAIL.TXT file with a lot of messages, in
which case it's well worth the wait just to have UNSEEN handled right.

