From: Rob Austein <SRA@XX.LCS.MIT.EDU>
To:   Bug-Babyl@MC.LCS.MIT.EDU
Subject: Header parsing

It seems that, for reasons that are beyond me, Babyl's header parsing
routine (!& Parse Header:!, invoked by !# Babyl R:! to get recipients)
is groveling the reformatted headers instead of the original headers.

Some time ago I wrote some code to generate modern (Message-ID based)
In-Reply-To headers, eg, instead of

In-reply-to: Msg of 21 Dec 1987 17:49-EST from Rob Austein <SRA@XX.LCS.MIT.EDU>

it generates

In-Reply-To: <SRA.12360349550.BABYL@XX.LCS.MIT.EDU>

(if it can't find the Message-ID it falls back to the old style).

I don't usually want to see Message-IDs, so they are removed by
reformatting.  This causes me to always get old-style In-Reply-To.

Is there any good reason why I shouldn't fix this by making the header
parser look at the uncensored headers?

--Rob

