Message-ID: <461908.880803.ZVONA@MC.LCS.MIT.EDU>

I've (finally) found at least one way of reproducing the problem which
causes babyl to get pdl overflow.  It's kind of obvious in retrospect.
A minimal case is: from babyl top level, type c-r c-x r c-r c-x r c-r
c-x r ... a few times and it'll blow out.  

Now that's a dumb things to do.  What I actually do that causes the
bug is to do c-r to get some text from the message, then c-x b to
change to another buffer, do some editing there, and then want to go
back to babyl mail-reading mode.  I could switch back to the message
buffer and do c-], but c-x r seems easier and more natural (it means
"get me to mail reading mode" intuitively).  

So I think this is a genuine bug and ought to be fixed.  I can't
imagine that babyl bugs are high on anyone's priority queue nowadays,
though... 

